      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Aftercare Instructions</h2>
        <p>Proper aftercare is crucial following ear irrigation to prevent complications and ensure optimal healing.</p>

        <div class="aftercare-sections">
          <div class="aftercare-immediate">
            <h3>Immediately After Treatment</h3>
            <div class="aftercare-grid">
              <div class="aftercare-item critical">
                <h4 class="critical-title">üö® CRITICAL</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>Keep your ears completely dry for 24-48 hours</li>
                  <li>Do not swim or submerge your head in water</li>
                  <li>Report severe pain, discharge, or hearing loss immediately</li>
                  <li>Allow any trapped water to drain naturally</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="aftercare-item recommended">
                <h4 class="recommended-title">‚úÖ RECOMMENDED</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>Gently tilt your head to help water drainage</li>
                  <li>Use a towel to dab (not rub) the outer ear</li>
                  <li>Take paracetamol if you experience mild discomfort</li>
                  <li>Rest if you feel dizzy or lightheaded</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="aftercare-first-week">
            <h3>First 48-72 Hours</h3>
            <div class="week-guidelines">
              <div class="guideline-item">
                <div class="guideline-icon">üöø</div>
                <div class="guideline-content">
                  <h4>Showering & Hair Washing</h4>
                  <p>Use cotton wool with petroleum jelly to seal ears completely. Consider postponing hair washing for 24-48 hours if possible.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="guideline-item">
                <div class="guideline-icon">üíß</div>
                <div class="guideline-content">
                  <h4>Water Activities</h4>
                  <p>Avoid swimming, diving, or any water sports. No baths where you might submerge your ears.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="guideline-item">
                <div class="guideline-icon">üëÇ</div>
                <div class="guideline-content">
                  <h4>Ear Care</h4>
                  <p>Never insert cotton buds, towels, or fingers into your ears. Let them air dry naturally.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="guideline-item">
                <div class="guideline-icon">‚ö†Ô∏è</div>
                <div class="guideline-content">
                  <h4>Warning Signs</h4>
                  <p>Watch for increasing pain, discharge, fever, or worsening hearing. Contact us immediately if these occur.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="aftercare-ongoing">
            <h3>Ongoing Care</h3>
            <div class="ongoing-care-tips">
              <div class="care-tip">
                <h4>üõ°Ô∏è Infection Prevention</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>Keep ears dry for at least one week</li>
                  <li>Avoid dusty or dirty environments if possible</li>
                  <li>Don't use earphones or hearing aids until cleared</li>
                  <li>Watch for signs of swimmer's ear (otitis externa)</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="care-tip">
                <h4>üîÑ Return to Normal Activities</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>Resume swimming after 1-2 weeks (if no complications)</li>
                  <li>Hearing aids can usually be reinserted after 24-48 hours</li>
                  <li>Exercise is fine, but avoid activities causing excessive sweating</li>
                  <li>Flying is generally safe after the first day</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="emergency-contacts">
          <h3>When to Seek Immediate Medical Attention</h3>
          <div class="emergency-symptoms">
            <div class="emergency-item urgent">
              <h4>üö® URGENT - Contact us immediately:</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Severe or worsening ear pain</li>
                <li>Discharge from the ear (especially if bloody or smelly)</li>
                <li>Sudden or significant hearing loss</li>
                <li>Signs of infection (fever, swelling, heat around ear)</li>
                <li>Persistent severe dizziness or balance problems</li>
                <li>Nausea and vomiting with ear symptoms</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Is Irrigation Right for You?</h2>
        <div class="suitability-assessment">
          <div class="suitable-candidates">
            <h3 class="suitable-title">‚úÖ Good Candidates for Irrigation</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Healthy eardrums with no history of perforation</li>
              <li>No current ear infections or inflammation</li>
              <li>Soft to medium-hard ear wax buildup</li>
              <li>No previous ear surgery or structural abnormalities</li>
              <li>Comfortable with water-based procedures</li>
              <li>Looking for cost-effective treatment option</li>
              <li>No significant balance or dizziness issues</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="unsuitable-candidates">
            <h3 class="unsuitable-title">‚ùå Not Suitable for Irrigation</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Known or suspected perforated eardrum</li>
              <li>Previous ear surgery or mastoid surgery</li>
              <li>Active ear infection or recent ear problems</li>
              <li>Hearing aids that cannot be removed</li>
              <li>Severe balance disorders or vertigo history</li>
              <li>Very hard or deeply impacted ear wax</li>
              <li>Anxiety about water-based procedures</li>
              <li>Immune system compromise</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="consultation-note">
          <p><strong>Important:</strong> A pre-treatment consultation is essential to determine if irrigation is safe and appropriate for your individual situation. Alternative methods may be recommended if irrigation is not suitable.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

